tool.name: TableToEllipse

param.name: Input_Table
param.dialogReference: Input table containing the source coordinates and input data values.
param.pythonReference: There is no python reference for this parameter.

param.name: Input_Coordinate_Format
param.expression: DD_2 | DD_1 | DDM_1 | DDM_2 | DMS_1 | DMS_2 | GARS | GEOREF | UTM_BANDS | UTM_ZONES | USNG | MGRS
param.pythonReference: There is no python reference for this parameter.
param.dialogReference:
Format of the Input Table coordinates. The default is DD_2.

  • DD_1 - Longitude and latitude coordinates formatted as Decimal Degrees that are in a single field with coordinates separated by a space, a comma, or a slash.

  • DD_2 - Longitude and latitude coordinates formatted as Decimal Degrees that are in two separate fields.

  • DDM_1 - Longitude and latitude coordinates formatted as Degree Decimal Minutes that are in a single field with coordinates separated by a space, a comma, or a slash.

  • DDM_2 - Longitude and latitude coordinates formatted as Degree Decimal Minutes that are in two separate fields.

  • DMS_1 - Longitude and latitude coordinates formatted as Degrees Minutes Seconds that are in a single field with coordinates separated by a space, a comma, or a slash.

  • DMS_2 - Longitude and latitude coordinates formatted as Degrees Minutes Seconds that are in two separate fields.

  • GARS - Global Area Reference System

  • GEOREF - World Geographic Reference System.

  • UTM_ZONES - Universal Transverse Mercator coordinate zones

  • UTM_BANDS - Universal Transverse Mercator coordinate bands

  • USNG—United States National Grid

  • MGRS—Military Grid Reference System

tool.summary: Creates ellipse features from tabular coordinates and input data values. This tool uses an input table with coordinate values for ellipse centers and values for major and minor axis lengths.
tool.usage: Output ellipse feature class will contain individual ellipses for each coordinate pair in the input table.
